      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Ruby McGregor-Smith joined the Department for Education as a non-executive board member in December 2015.</p>

<p>Ruby was formerly the Chief Executive of the Mitie Group, a strategic outsourcing company, and was the first Asian woman to be appointed to such a role in the <abbr title="Financial Times Stock Exchange">FTSE</abbr> 250 or <abbr title="Financial Times Stock Exchange">FTSE</abbr> 100. Ruby has also been the chair of the Womenâ€™s Business Council and a non-executive board member at the Department for Culture, Media and Sport.</p>

<p>Ruby received a <abbr title="Commander of the Order of the British Empire">CBE</abbr> for services to business and diversity in business in 2012 and was a created a life peer in 2015.</p>

</div>
      </section>

